          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The detector used was a nominal 100% relative",
                "efficiency high-purity germanium detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The source was placed inside of a lead and",
                "tungsten box with a tungsten collimator to form a",
                "0.51-cm-diameter beam. The active diameter of the",
                "source material is 0.53 cm. The beam then passes",
                "through a mechanical sample holder/changer that",
                "contains the four sample thicknesses, plus a blank.",
                "Each of the four sample positions is moved into the",
                "beam for one minute at a time, with a complete cycle",
                "of all four positions taking just over five minutes",
                "with various overheads. The samples were run for",
                "between two and seven days each, in order to",
                "accumulate the statistics necessary to allow the",
                "cross section to be measured at the 0.5% 3 level at",
                "the 3.451 MeV line. For ease of storage, handling,",
                "and analysis, the data were accumulated into  runs",
                "of approximately one day each, and the data was then",
                "analyzed on a run-by-run basis. HPGe detector was used",
                "to detect transmitted photons."
              ]
            }
          ],
